Root cause of 'the new skeletons never fire from scratch': the selection
surfaces never learned them. A regenerated engine changes nothing if
deck-strategy cannot NAME the forms.

- deck-strategy Step 3 job table: add identity / identity+sub (STRAC) /
  breakeven rows — the primary beat->pattern surface.
- deck-strategy Step 3b: fix the 額装 trap the skill itself taught
  (コスト=固定費+変動費 was listed as a formula example): formula '+' is for
  TERM relations only; a sum whose magnitudes/内訳 matter is an identity.
  Add full identity/breakeven gate bullets (symbol-erasure, all-or-none,
  STRAC nesting, protagonist=残り).
- deck-strategy Step 3.0 (new, MUST): docs/canon/*.md lookup promoted from a
  parenthetical to a numbered step; catalog rows OVERRIDE own judgment for
  matching concepts; fired row recorded in notes; search repo root too
  (mono-repo deck folders).
- education-register §2-1: structure-word vocabulary gains identity(恒等式/
  内訳/構成), bridge, crossing; skeleton list gains identity/breakeven with
  the formula-vs-identity rule.
- design-lint: formula operator '+' -> INFO nudge toward identity (machine
  backstop for the trap); struct words +内訳|分岐.
- deck-brief 構成 slot + usecases/seminar.md: canon awareness.
- day1-deck/theme-daikichi.json: brand theme (navy x gold, CONTRAST-lint
  calibrated: accent=755A0D dark gold under white text, accentSoft=C9A227
  brand gold, accentOnDark=E4CE7A, warn=C7431D).

run-gate PASS all themes; nudge fire verified on 資産=負債+純資産 formula.
